Question: Overextending and demotivating delegates are the two main risks to avoid when delegating tasks.

Match the risks to examples of ways to avoid them. Each risk matches to more than one example.
Instruction: Match each option with its correct target. Each category has a single match. 
Answer Choices
A:Demotivating
B:Overextending
Options

Try to achieve a balance between the task delegated and the delegate

A

B

Don't give a delegate an overwhelming amount of responsibility

A

B

Try to assign novel tasks that bring new challenges

A

B

Don't ask someone to take on a task they'll likely find terribly boring

A

B
